<A NAME="getColor(java.lang.String, java.lang.String)"><!-- --></A><H3>
getColor</H3>
<PRE>
public static java.awt.Color <B>getColor</B>(java.lang.String&nbsp;key,
                                      java.lang.String&nbsp;def)</PRE>
<DL>
<DD>Returns the color configured for the specified key. The key 
 will be prepended with "tetris.color." and the value will be
 read from the system properties. The color value must be 
 specified in hexadecimal web format, i.e. in the "#RRGGBB" 
 format. If the default color isn't in a valid format, white 
 will be returned.<DD><DL>
<DT><B>Parameters:</B><DD><CODE>key</CODE> - the configuration parameter key<DD><CODE>def</CODE> - the default value<DT><B>Returns:</B><DD>the color specified in the configuration, or 
         a default color value</DL>
</DD>
</DL>
